    {
      "text": "A 55-year-old woman presents with bone pain, recurrent infections, elevated serum calcium levels, renal dysfunction, and anaemia. Laboratory tests reveal an M spike on serum protein electrophoresis and the presence of Bence Jones proteins in the urine. Based on this presentation, which of the following is not a criterion for a myeloma-defining event in the diagnostic criteria for this condition?",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "Hypercalcemia",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "Anemia",
